# [HAPPY](../wg/happy.html)

## Summary

The HAPPY working group met at IETF 126 to discuss updates to the core Happy Eyeballs specification, review implementation reports from three major web browsers, and consider proposals for optimistic DNS, connection testing, and error reporting. 

The main focus of the meeting was progressing [draft-ietf-happy-happyeyeballs-v3](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-happy-happyeyeballs-v3/), resolving outstanding issues on NAT64/IPv6-only networks, and addressing how the protocol interacts with split-tunnel VPNs. The chairs noted that despite missing the original July charter target, the working group is in a strong position to finalize the draft soon and proceed toward a Working Group Last Call (WGLC) after resolving outstanding pull requests.

