* **Presenter:** Johannes Zirngibl
* **Slides:** [Happy Eyeballs Webtester](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-happy-happy-eyeballs-webtester-00)
* **Technical Details:**
  * The web-based testing framework has been updated to support HEv3 tests (available on a staging site).
  * It tests client behaviors by delaying server hellos (at the TLS/QUIC handshake layer) or network-layer packets based on IP family and protocol.
  * Recent additions from the IETF 126 Hackathon include server-side packet capturing and DNS query arrival logging to reconstruct precise connection traces.
  * Added test cases for HTTP/3 detection, Encrypted Client Hello (ECH) fallback, HTTPS alias mode behavior, and asynchronous handling of delayed AAAA records.

